      "content": "it feels like those \"operational adjustments\" usually just mean i have to cut people's hours or let someone go. i also see a lot of people online saying that raising the wage is just a way to help people's dignity and spend more in the local economy. do you think the \"dignity\" argument holds up for a small shop like mine, or is that just something politicians say?",
